  {
    "query": "Are TechFin and Ancillary Service Providers permitted to perform the services listed in the Third Schedule of the IFSCA (TechFin and Ancillary Services) Regulations, 2025?",
    "golden_answer": "No. According to the explanation provided in clause (xiii) of Section 3, TechFin and Ancillary Service Providers registered under these regulations are explicitly prohibited from undertaking any of the services specified in the Third Schedule.",
    "target_node_id": "ed12cd55-6683-40d6-bc95-a418b1f6b0af",
    "category": "Cross-Reference",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (TechFin and Ancillary Services) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter I - Preliminary > Section 3 -> IFSCA (TechFin and Ancillary Services) Regulations, 2025 > The Third Schedule"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (TechFin and Ancillary Services) Regulations, 2025, what criteria must be met for an entity to be considered part of 'Group Entities'?",
    "golden_answer": "According to the regulations, 'Group Entities' includes an arrangement involving two or more entities related to each other through any of the following relationships: (a) parent-subsidiary (as per Ind-AS 110/AS 21); (b) joint venture (as per Ind-AS 28/AS 27); (c) associate (as per Ind-AS 28/AS 23); (d) common brand name; (e) investment in equity shares/capital contribution of 20 per cent and above; or (f) being part of a network, where 'network' is defined as a larger structure of firms that pool resources, share uniform policies, technology, and collaterals, and operate as one unit with a lead firm.",
    "target_node_id": "ed12cd55-6683-40d6-bc95-a418b1f6b0af",
    "category": "Glossary Definition",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (TechFin and Ancillary Services) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter I - Preliminary > Section 3 > Ancillary Services"
  },
  {
    "query": "What are the obligations of a capital market intermediary regarding a client's risk profile under the IFSCA (Capital Market Intermediaries) Regulations, 2025?",
    "golden_answer": "Under the regulations, a capital market intermediary must communicate the client's risk profile to the client once the risk assessment is completed and ensure that the information provided by the client and their risk assessment are updated periodically.",
    "target_node_id": "bb4b2291-1a3b-4839-af4f-d652cdc0ec88",
    "category": "Direct Regulation",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Capital Market Intermediaries) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter IV - SPECIFIC OBLIGATIONS AND RESPONSIBILITES > Section 34 > Clause"
  },
  {
    "query": "What is the requirement for an FME operating as a branch in an IFSC if it obtains approval from its home regulator for activities outside of those specified in the IFSCA regulations?",
    "golden_answer": "An FME operating as a branch in an IFSC must inform the Authority within fifteen (15) days regarding any approval obtained from its home regulator.",
    "target_node_id": "1921305a-4b0f-40e7-993e-1529f35276fd",
