    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter IX - Inspection and Audit > Section 138 > (1)"
  },
  {
    "query": "Who is responsible for valuing the assets of a scheme under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, and are there any exceptions to this requirement?",
    "golden_answer": "The assets of a scheme must be valued by an independent service provider, such as a fund administrator, a custodian, a credit rating agency registered with the Authority, a valuer registered with the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India, or another person specified by the Authority. An exception applies to fund of funds schemes that invest in schemes regulated by a financial sector regulator (either in IFSC, India, or a foreign jurisdiction) that are already valued by an independent entity.",
    "target_node_id": "cf46c484-0e58-4b60-823d-58a03de20e0e",
    "category": "Cross-Reference",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter III - Schemes for Fund Management > Section 26 -> IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Sixth Schedule"
  },
  {
    "query": "What specific operational requirements must an applicant commit to regarding the location of key activities and personnel under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025?",
    "golden_answer": "Applicants must ensure that key activities, specifically investment decisions, portfolio management, and grievance handling, are undertaken from the IFSC. Additionally, they must ensure that all Key Management Personnel, as required under regulation 7, are based out of the IFSC.",
    "target_node_id": "80ea95a9-b1fe-45dc-b3e8-2b1c8b2af885",
    "category": "Direct Regulation",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > First Schedule > Schedule"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (Banking) Regulations, 2020, what is the distinction between an 'IFSC Banking Company' (IBC) and an 'IFSC Banking Unit' (IBU)?",
    "golden_answer": "An 'IFSC Banking Company' (IBC) is a Banking Unit licensed or permitted by the Authority to operate in an IFSC as a subsidiary company of the Parent Bank, whereas an 'IFSC Banking Unit' (IBU) is a Banking Unit licensed or permitted by the Authority to operate in an IFSC as a branch of the Parent Bank.",
    "target_node_id": "c385283d-bb08-4bcc-bf6a-59a9552590a7",
    "category": "Glossary Definition",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Banking) Regulations, 2020 > Chapter I - Preliminary > Section 2 > Act"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the International Financial Services Centres Authority Act, 2019, how is a 'financial institution' defined?",
    "golden_answer": "A 'financial institution' is defined as a unit established within an International Financial Services Centre that is engaged in providing financial services related to any financial product.",
