  },
  {
    "query": "What are the specific requirements for an individual to be designated as a compliance officer under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025?",
    "golden_answer": "To be designated as a compliance officer, an individual must be a senior officer who reports directly to the board of directors (or the head of the organization if no board exists) and must possess the capability to understand financial statements and the relevant legal and regulatory requirements.",
