  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, what specific legal or enforcement circumstances regarding economic offences would disqualify a person from registration?",
    "golden_answer": "A person is disqualified if there is a pending case filed against them by an Indian enforcement agency concerning economic offences, if charges have been framed against them by a court of law or equivalent institution for economic offences, or if a recovery proceeding has been initiated against them.",
    "target_node_id": "37ea88ce-c9f2-45f3-8c10-d116d88977ad",
    "category": "Direct Regulation",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter II - REGISTRATION OF FUND MANAGEMENT ENTITY (FME) > Section 9 > Clause"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, what criteria must a person meet to be designated as a 'compliance officer' for a fund management entity?",
    "golden_answer": "A compliance officer must be a senior officer designated by the entity and report to the board of directors (or the head of the organization if no board exists). They must be capable of understanding financial statements and the requirements for legal and regulatory compliance under the regulations. Their responsibilities include ensuring compliance with policies and procedures, maintaining records, monitoring adherence to rules regarding unpublished price sensitive information, monitoring trades, managing risk, and implementing the codes specified in the regulations, all under the overall supervision of the board of directors or the head of the organization.",
    "target_node_id": "e2cb51bd-0ce8-4dc1-8662-4e3f6ce5fff3",
    "category": "Glossary Definition",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter I - Preliminary > Section 2 > fund management entity (FME)"
  },
  {
    "query": "What conditions must an FME satisfy when creating a segregated portfolio for co-investments within a restricted scheme?",
    "golden_answer": "When creating a segregated portfolio, the FME must ensure that the investments made by the segregated portfolio are not on terms more favorable than those offered to the common portfolio of the restricted scheme, and that appropriate disclosures regarding the creation of the segregated portfolio are included in the placement memorandum.",
    "target_node_id": "d5182baa-a73a-466b-a211-78dc5ceb77b6",
    "category": "Direct Regulation",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter II > Section 41"
  },
  {
    "query": "What are the specific obligations of a Fund Management Entity (FME) regarding the valuation of investments in its schemes?",
    "golden_answer": "Under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, an FME is required to compute and carry out the valuation of investments made by its schemes in accordance with the investment valuation norms specified in the Sixth Schedule and must publish these valuations. Furthermore, the FME and its controlling shareholders are liable to compensate the scheme or affected investors for any unfair treatment resulting from inappropriate valuation.",
    "target_node_id": "655f98ec-a79a-4790-8f55-cf0cfd102032",
    "category": "Cross-Reference",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Third Schedule > Schedule -> IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Sixth Schedule"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, how is a 'family investment fund' defined?",
    "golden_answer": "A 'family investment fund' is defined as a fund that pools money exclusively from a single family through one or more investment vehicles, and which has been established in accordance with the provisions of these regulations.",
    "target_node_id": "e2cb51bd-0ce8-4dc1-8662-4e3f6ce5fff3",
    "category": "Glossary Definition",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter I - Preliminary > Section 2 > family investment fund"
  },
  {
    "query": "What are the specific purposes for which the Authority may appoint an inspecting authority to conduct an inspection of a Capital Market Intermediary (CMI)?",
    "golden_answer": "The Authority may appoint an inspecting authority to: (a) ensure books, records, and documents are maintained as required; (b) ensure compliance with the Act, regulations, and circulars; (c) verify the adequacy of internal control systems, procedures, and safeguards; (d) determine if the intermediary remains fit or eligible; (e) investigate complaints from investors, clients, or other market participants; and (f) conduct suo motu inquiries deemed necessary in the interest of investors or the capital market in an IFSC.",
    "target_node_id": "a00304f0-b0d4-4594-80a2-1a8e8f34a84e",
    "category": "Cross-Reference",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Capital Market Intermediaries) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter V - Inspection > Section 37 -> IFSCA (Capital Market Intermediaries) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter V - Inspection > Section 37 > (2)"
  },
  {
    "query": "What types of ancillary services are included under the scope of the IFSCA (TechFin and Ancillary Services) Regulations, 2025?",
    "golden_answer": "The services include housekeeping, civil, mechanical, electrical, and plumbing maintenance, other outsourced manpower services, transport and logistics, construction-related services, management of physical assets, and any other services deemed appropriate by the Authority.",
