  {
    "query": "Is the inspecting authority required to provide prior notice to a Capital Market Intermediary (CMI) before conducting an inspection, and are there any exceptions to this requirement?",
    "golden_answer": "Yes, the inspecting authority is generally required to give notice to the CMI before undertaking an inspection. However, if the inspecting authority determines that it is in the interest of investors to proceed without notice, they may dispense with the requirement, provided they record the reasons for doing so in writing.",
    "target_node_id": "a00304f0-b0d4-4594-80a2-1a8e8f34a84e",
