  },
  {
    "query": "What criteria must a sponsor meet to be considered as having a 'sound track record' under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025?",
    "golden_answer": "To have a 'sound track record', a sponsor must possess at least five years of relevant experience, and if the sponsor is a developer, they must have completed at least two projects.",
    "target_node_id": "7bfc53bb-78a2-4df5-9448-10dcb5666ffb",
    "category": "Direct Regulation",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > PART B: INVESTMENT TRUST > Section 86 > Clause"
  },
  {
    "query": "What is the deadline for completing the half-yearly valuation report for an Investment Trust, and what period must it cover?",
    "golden_answer": "The half-yearly valuation report must be prepared within one month from the end of the half-year period, which concludes on September 30, and it must incorporate any key changes that occurred during the preceding six months.",
    "target_node_id": "10c2f5b7-3303-42cf-812b-13641cd44a08",
    "category": "Direct Regulation",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > PART B: INVESTMENT TRUST > Section 102 > (2)"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, what are the grounds upon which the Authority may take action, such as suspension or cancellation of registration, against a Fund Management Entity (FME)?",
    "golden_answer": "The Authority may take action against an FME if it: (a) fails to exercise due diligence or comply with registration conditions; (b) contravenes any provisions of the Act, rules, regulations, circulars, guidelines, or directions; (c) fails to furnish requested information; (d) provides false or misleading information; (e) fails to submit periodic returns or reports; (f) does not cooperate in enquiries, inspections, or investigations; (g) fails to resolve investor complaints or provide satisfactory replies to the Authority; or (h) commits any other act or omission that the Authority deems warrants action or is contrary to the interests of investors.",
    "target_node_id": "b2e4d986-df07-4bba-8486-b2689ec549ec",
    "category": "Cross-Reference",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter X - Liability for action in case of default > Section 143 -> IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter X - Liability for action in case of default"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, what specific criteria must a pre-COD infrastructure project meet to be considered an 'eligible infrastructure project'?",
    "golden_answer": "For a pre-COD project to qualify as an 'eligible infrastructure project', it must meet two conditions: (i) it has not yet achieved its commercial operation date (COD) as defined under its relevant project agreements (such as concession or power purchase agreements); and (ii) it must have either completed at least 50% of the project construction as certified by an independent engineer, or have expended at least 50% of the total capital cost specified in the financial package of the relevant project agreement.",
    "target_node_id": "19fea583-e9e4-4ae6-a527-52f79685f113",
    "category": "Cross-Reference",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > PART B: INVESTMENT TRUST > Section 83 -> IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > FOURTH SCHEDULE"
  },
  {
    "query": "If a capital market intermediary operates under multiple categories, how should it determine its minimum net worth requirement?",
    "golden_answer": "If an entity operates as a capital market intermediary in multiple categories, it must maintain the highest of the applicable minimum net worth requirements, unless the Authority specifies otherwise.",
    "target_node_id": "4479dcaa-5466-4eea-9a5f-ca5ef59050e2",
    "category": "Cross-Reference",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Capital Market Intermediaries) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter II - Registration of Capital Market Intermediaries > Section 7 -> IFSCA (Capital Market Intermediaries) Regulations, 2025 > Schedule I"
  },
  {
    "query": "What are the requirements for a Fund Management Entity (FME) if it intends to change its registration category?",
    "golden_answer": "An FME that has been granted a certificate of registration under a specific category is prohibited from changing its category unless it obtains prior approval from the Authority.",
    "target_node_id": "72f8dca7-d3ed-44ab-8849-3a638c0468d4",
    "category": "Direct Regulation",
    "breadcrumb": "IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025 > Chapter II - REGISTRATION OF FUND MANAGEMENT ENTITY (FME) > Section 13"
  },
  {
    "query": "Under the IFSCA (Fund Management) Regulations, 2025, how is a 'trust' defined?",
    "golden_answer": "A 'trust' is defined as a trust established under the Indian Trusts Act, 1882, or under an Act of Parliament or State Legislation.",
    "target_node_id": "e2cb51bd-0ce8-4dc1-8662-4e3f6ce5fff3",
    "category": "Glossary Definition",
